      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOFT WHISPER (1) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when second (23.44) at The Gardens. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Makes plenty of appeal. RUN ROLEX (2) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 7 length second (17.88) in a Grade 5 at Taree Super Track. Leading player again. BAD KNEES (7) boasts strong form at this distance having won two times from three starts. Comes off a (22.52) win last time, scoring by 4.5 lengths in a Grade 5 over 400m at this track. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. ZIPPING PERCAT (8) should be thereabouts.",
